(This is often generated using Lombok @Builder)

Lombok Builder (Industry Standard)
import lombok.Builder;
import lombok.Data;

@Data
@Builder
public class Employee {

    private int id;
    private String name;
    private String email;
}

Usage:

Employee emp = Employee.builder()
        .id(101)
        .name("Sunil")
        .email("test@gmail.com")
        .build();
Advantages

✔ Improves readability
✔ Handles many parameters easily
✔ Supports optional fields
✔ Immutable object creation
✔ Avoids telescoping constructors

When to Use Builder Pattern?

✔ When object has many fields
✔ When many fields are optional
✔ When you want immutable objects
✔ When constructor becomes unreadable

